1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,100
<i> You're an actor, Amo!</i>

2
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:13,833
<i> You're so good at pretending.</i>

3
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:15,700
<i> Take Amo away!</i>

4
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:17,100
<i> I said drop that!</i>

5
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:23,267
<i> Lieutenant Conde?</i>

6
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,167
<i> Thank you for saving me.</i>

7
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:26,900
<i>It's a good thing I hired you
as a bodyguard.</i>

8
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:30,233
<i>Just say you took advantage of
Lieutenant Conde's suspension!</i>

9
00:00:30,367 --> 00:00:31,467
<i> Enriquez!</i>

10
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,700
<i>That's why I got suspended,
right, because of you?</i>

11
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:34,367
<i>And now, you're going
to insult my father.</i>

12
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:36,433
<i>You understand me. You're a cop.</i>

13
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:39,467
<i>It's your obligation
to protect people,</i>

14
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,133
<i>especially those who
are important to you.</i>

15
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,733
<i> Be careful with your actions.</i>

16
00:00:42,867 --> 00:00:46,100
<i>I don't want my plans to be
ruined by a suspended cop.</i>

17
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:48,733
<i>We don't have a solid case
to get a search warrant.</i>

18
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:50,733
<i>Enriquez,
just trust the process.</i>

19
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:53,500
<i>Why did Chief say
trust the process?</i>

20
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:54,267
<i> What does that mean?</i>

21
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,133
<i>Thank you for calling me father.</i>

22
00:00:56,267 --> 00:00:58,067
<i> It's my job to protect you.</i>

23
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,567
<i> I trust you completely.</i>

24
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:02,133
<i> My landlady is calling.</i>

25
00:01:02,267 --> 00:01:03,200
<i> Hello, Ms. Tess?</i>

26
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:04,000
<i> How are you?</i>

27
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:05,233
<i>I'm just getting started, Chief.</i>

28
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:07,200
<i>He can't find out that you're
working undercover.</i>

29
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:08,567
<i> Maybe he's just testing you.</i>

30
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:11,233
<i>I wouldn't hesitate
to have my father jailed.</i>

31
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:12,867
<i> Be careful, Conde.</i>

32
00:01:16,433 --> 00:01:17,467
Come in.

33
00:01:28,267 --> 00:01:29,700
Did you watch this?

34
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:32,500
Probably not.

35
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,633
It's not as popular
as the others,

36
00:01:34,767 --> 00:01:36,133
but it's one of my favorites.

37
00:01:38,033 --> 00:01:39,967
Why is it your favorite?

38
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,867
I thought of that story.

39
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:45,967
I helped write the script

40
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:48,767
even though I didn't know
anything about scriptwriting.

41
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,100
Well, after that,
I didn't want any more.

42
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,400
It was hard.

43
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:54,500
But...

44
00:01:56,633 --> 00:01:59,167
you know, all of them,
they're my favorites.

45
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,633
Those are like my children.

46
00:02:05,467 --> 00:02:06,700
I'm sorry, Tonyo.

47
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:11,467
I think I said something wrong.

48
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:16,767
What?

49
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:23,667
Did you consider your movies
more like children than me?

50
00:02:26,667 --> 00:02:27,800
That's okay.

51
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,733
That's not okay, Tonyo.

52
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,433
I admit it.

53
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:39,000
I valued fame and being an actor
more.

54
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:42,667
I thought that was all that
mattered.

55
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:45,933
It was too late when I realized

56
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,867
that all of these things would
disappear.

57
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:55,100
I wish my family had been
my priority,

58
00:02:56,967 --> 00:02:58,167
especially you.

59
00:03:05,633 --> 00:03:06,267
Tonyo,

60
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:09,433
can I hug you?

61
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:38,833
By the way.
I just need to text something.

62
00:03:38,967 --> 00:03:39,633
Wait a minute?

63
00:04:22,467 --> 00:04:23,067
Come in.

64
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:24,667
Amo...

65
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,100
Sir, hello.

66
00:04:26,233 --> 00:04:27,633
Amo, your tarps.

67
00:04:29,867 --> 00:04:30,933
Roman.

68
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:33,733
Did you hear about what happened
yesterday at the market?

69
00:04:33,867 --> 00:04:34,533
Yes.

70
00:04:34,667 --> 00:04:36,333
Verns told me.

71
00:04:36,467 --> 00:04:38,300
You're lucky, Tonyo.

72
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,867
My son is really good.

73
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:46,433
Amo, sorry, excuse me I need you
to sign something, and that...

74
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:48,533
Sign, sign, sign.
We can do that later.

75
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:49,233
Let's do that later.

76
00:04:49,367 --> 00:04:50,567
Okay, come with me outside.

77
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,367
Okay, Amo, sorry.

78
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,033
Okay, I'll leave you here
for now.

79
00:04:54,167 --> 00:04:55,567
Come on, come on.
Let's go upstairs.

80
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:55,900
Yes, by the way, Amo.

81
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:58,667
Did you get the email
from the Attorney?

82
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:02,533
He said he's already drafted
the election complaint,

83
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:04,767
the one for Mayor Guerrero.

84
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,133
Not yet, but...

85
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,567
Can you give me my cellphone?

86
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:10,367
Wait a minute.

87
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:12,600
Where is it, Amo? Here?

88
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,133
Amo, it's not here.

89
00:06:16,267 --> 00:06:16,767
Nothing?

90
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:20,000
Look downstairs.
Maybe I left it there.

91
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:21,733
This is hard.

92
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:23,833
I'm getting forgetful.

93
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,600
Do you want me to ring your
phone, Amo?

94
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:29,033
Okay, okay.

95
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:29,833
Wait a minute.

96
00:06:29,967 --> 00:06:32,200
But, maybe it's just here.

97
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,433
Amo, it cannot be reached.

98
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,367
Ring it again.

99
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:44,900
Nothing, sir.

100
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:46,900
Amo,

101
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:50,133
your cell phone isn't
downstairs.

102
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:52,433
Cell phone?

103
00:06:52,567 --> 00:06:53,267
This?

104
00:06:56,867 --> 00:06:58,567
It wasn't there earlier, Amo.

105
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:01,633
Oh my, Roman.

106
00:07:01,767 --> 00:07:03,800
You're using your mouth
to look for it.

107
00:07:05,267 --> 00:07:06,167
Hey, here it is.

108
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,667
What's this? Dead battery?

109
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,800
That's why it won't ring.

110
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,533
I'll just charge it.

111
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:15,633
Come with me.

112
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:35,600
Roman!

113
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,467
Tonyo, have you seen Roman?

114
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,067
Not yet, Father.

115
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,467
Maybe he's still upstairs.

116
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,133
Do you have any orders?

117
00:07:45,267 --> 00:07:47,067
No, I was just going to ask him
to bring this.

118
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,167
I'll do it.

119
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,467
No need, Tonyo.

120
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:52,900
Roman is filing my confidential
documents.

121
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:58,567
He also holds the key and,
to ease my mind.

122
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:02,233
I have some visitors coming
later.

123
00:08:02,367 --> 00:08:05,233
The women's group
from the barangays.

124
00:08:06,567 --> 00:08:08,033
I want to introduce you.

125
00:08:09,367 --> 00:08:10,700
Can you stay for a while?

126
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:14,467
Can I just come back later?

127
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:17,500
Because I still need
to see our landlady.

128
00:08:18,867 --> 00:08:19,467
Okay, okay.

129
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:20,833
Come on, I'll walk you out.

130
00:08:22,733 --> 00:08:23,333
Amo!

131
00:08:25,133 --> 00:08:26,267
You're looking for me?

132
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,033
You go ahead.

133
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:32,300
Please file this.

134
00:08:32,433 --> 00:08:33,367
I'll take care of it.

135
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:05,233
Why are you calling?

136
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:08,967
Based on what Selena said,

137
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:11,533
there's someone here with us who
works for Amo.

138
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:14,633
What I need to know is whether
or not the officer

139
00:09:14,767 --> 00:09:15,667
is indeed one of Amo's henchmen.

140
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:49,333
It's a miracle,
you're the one calling now.

141
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:51,800
Is there a problem?

142
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,000
Wait, wait, wait.

143
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:56,100
Not here, not here.

144
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:57,400
It's hard to talk here.

145
00:09:57,533 --> 00:09:59,100
One of your policemen is here.

146
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:00,467
Let's meet.

147
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:02,333
Okay.

148
00:11:10,667 --> 00:11:12,167
What's the update with Tonyo?

149
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:15,633
He's clean.

150
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:18,233
He's defending Amo
at the precinct.

151
00:11:18,367 --> 00:11:20,400
I'm pissed off with him.

152
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:27,933
Just don't give him any reason
to suspect you.

153
00:11:28,067 --> 00:11:29,067
Befriend him.

154
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:31,433
He likes to drink.

155
00:11:33,967 --> 00:11:35,933
But we have another problem.

156
00:11:36,067 --> 00:11:37,233
What's that?

157
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:39,433
One of our police colleagues

158
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:41,300
is hot-blooded towards Amo...

159
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:43,733
Enriquez.

160
00:11:43,867 --> 00:11:44,867
I know her.

161
00:11:46,433 --> 00:11:47,700
I have to go.

162
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,067
Do you have something for me?

163
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:52,133
I thought you forgot.

164
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:53,633
There's still change.

165
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:20,167
- Boss Tonyo!
- Right!

166
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,867
What's with you?
You're wrong timing!

167
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,133
What's wrong? I'm working.
You're bothering me!

168
00:12:24,267 --> 00:12:26,333
We've only seen you once,
and you're like that.

169
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:27,533
Wait, wait.

170
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:29,767
Do you see any familiar faces
here from Station 12?

171
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:31,367
No, Boss, you're the only one
from...

172
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,533
That's a long way from here.

173
00:12:32,667 --> 00:12:34,400
Who's going to come here
from there?

174
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:36,067
It's just because there's
this woman here, Boss.

175
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:36,933
Boss, treat us.

176
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:37,867
What?

177
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,300
We're hungry.

178
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:40,033
Tonyo?

179
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,367
What are you doing here?

180
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:46,933
Roman,

181
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:51,233
I'm meeting my friends here.

182
00:12:52,333 --> 00:12:53,600
Yes, Sir.

183
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:56,233
Okay.

184
00:12:56,367 --> 00:12:57,367
Oh, what?

185
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,033
Just go to the place you said
you would.

186
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:00,900
I'll follow you there.

187
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:01,700
Boss?

188
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:02,567
Follow, Boss?

189
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:03,833
Follow, Boss?

190
00:13:03,967 --> 00:13:05,233
We don't have any money
to pay for that.

191
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:05,833
Go ahead!

192
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:06,667
Boss, huh.

193
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:13,100
You know, Tonyo, we made
a mistake at the beginning.

194
00:13:13,233 --> 00:13:14,633
You're so arrogant.

195
00:13:15,667 --> 00:13:17,867
Well, sorry.

196
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,700
I've already bought some snacks.

197
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:21,867
You're doing a good job.

198
00:13:22,033 --> 00:13:24,400
I have fifteen-year-old alcohol
waiting at home.

199
00:13:24,533 --> 00:13:26,233
Let's just have a drink.

200
00:13:26,367 --> 00:13:28,333
Okay? Let's go. Go ahead.

201
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:48,933
Okay, well, you know what you're
going to do?

202
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:50,967
Just distract them, okay?

203
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,967
Sergeant Enriquez,
where are you going?

204
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,200
What are you going to do?

205
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,467
Well, I'll take care of it.

206
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,600
Okay, let's go, let's go,
let's go.

207
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:03,833
Go ahead and drink that!

208
00:14:06,367 --> 00:14:08,233
Finish that?

209
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:09,400
Drink it.

210
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:13,400
Okay, okay.

211
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:15,233
Go back there, go back there.

212
00:14:15,367 --> 00:14:17,267
Amo will see you later.

213
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:20,667
Roman is such a killjoy.

214
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,533
They need to know who
the boss is.

215
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:26,467
That's legal.

216
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,233
Okay, so it's just the two
of us.

217
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,300
Come on, shot.

218
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:32,900
Is that okay?

219
00:14:34,433 --> 00:14:36,033
Where did you put it?

220
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:47,867
What were you doing
at the street market earlier?

221
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:51,300
Are you meeting someone there?

222
00:14:51,433 --> 00:14:57,267
You know, this is popular there.
These intestines and Betamax.

223
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,567
This is my favorite.

224
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:00,133
Wait, wait...

225
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:03,000
Show me how...

226
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:05,433
You turned the hose into darts.

227
00:15:05,567 --> 00:15:07,700
I almost died there. Almost.

228
00:15:22,933 --> 00:15:24,567
Girl...

229
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:26,167
I'm nervous.

230
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,567
It's my first time pretending.

231
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:30,467
Hey, what first time?

232
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,967
We've been pretending our whole
lives.

233
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:34,533
We even became a guard.

234
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:35,767
And you're nervous now?

235
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:36,667
That's right, right?

236
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,667
Okay, just keep it simple, okay?

237
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:48,767
Don't be nervous, you'll be even
more noticeable.

238
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,367
How did you do it?

239
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:57,367
Wait, wait.

240
00:15:58,767 --> 00:15:59,600
What's wrong with you?

241
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:01,167
Wait, wait, wait.

242
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:03,133
It's not fair.

243
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:05,367
There are three of you.

244
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,433
Is that three?

245
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,067
You're three.

246
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:11,833
That's why you win at drinking
sprees.

247
00:16:11,967 --> 00:16:14,867
Well, just like you, it's like
there are two of you.

248
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:15,767
Only two?

249
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:17,233
We're not enough.

250
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:19,000
Sit down. Let's drink more.

251
00:16:19,133 --> 00:16:19,767
Drink more!

252
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:22,300
Okay, finish that.

253
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:23,267
Are you done already?

254
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:25,000
Finish that. What's done yet?

255
00:16:45,967 --> 00:16:46,867
Wait,

256
00:16:49,433 --> 00:16:50,533
it's coming back.

257
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,533
I'm just going to lie down.

258
00:16:55,667 --> 00:16:56,733
Lie down for a bit.

259
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:00,400
Just a moment?

260
00:17:00,533 --> 00:17:01,400
Roman...

261
00:17:04,567 --> 00:17:06,633
Are you okay?

262
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:09,267
I think you're going to sleep?
Are you asleep already?

263
00:17:15,933 --> 00:17:18,067
Okay, what do you want?

264
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,700
Yes, I'll buy it later.

265
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,567
Yes, I'll take care of it.

266
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:22,500
Okay.

267
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:43,033
Thank you very much for coming.

268
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,200
Thank you very much
for your time.

269
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:48,267
And of course, don't forget.
Amo for mayor.

270
00:17:48,433 --> 00:17:49,233
Thank you very much, Ma'am.

271
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:50,867
Yes, take care on your way home.

272
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,800
- Thank you!
- Yes, Thank you too.

273
00:17:52,933 --> 00:17:53,900
Take care on your way home.

274
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:54,467
Okay.

275
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,200
Ma'am, good evening.

276
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:57,900
Good evening.

277
00:17:58,033 --> 00:17:58,867
Hello.

278
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,167
What do you need?

279
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,233
We were going to solicit
from Amo.

280
00:18:03,367 --> 00:18:08,167
Well, we're going to organize
a community defense workshop.

281
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:10,700
And we're members of

282
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:12,867
the Shining Shimmering Friends
of Amo here in Calabari.

283
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,533
- Yes. Yeah, true.
- Right, Abdul?

284
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:17,067
Shining Shimmering Friends,
really?

285
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,967
Yes, actually, we are one
of Amo's fan clubs.

286
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:21,733
Eh, right, Mar?

287
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:25,533
Maybe we can talk to Amo?

288
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:27,433
We just have some explaining
to do.

289
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:28,400
That's the thing.

290
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:30,933
Thank you, but Amo is resting
already.

291
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:32,100
We're very busy today.

292
00:18:32,233 --> 00:18:34,133
Maybe tomorrow, Sir?

293
00:18:34,267 --> 00:18:36,733
Even if it's just
for a little while.

294
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:37,800
Yes?

295
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:39,700
No problem with Amo,
as long as it's tomorrow.

296
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:40,500
Amo?

297
00:18:40,633 --> 00:18:41,933
Who are you talking to?

298
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:43,567
Idol!

299
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:44,600
Oh my, good evening!

300
00:18:44,733 --> 00:18:46,000
Good evening to you.

301
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:47,533
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

302
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:49,900
You're really handsome
in person, right?

303
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:51,533
What can I do for you?

304
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:54,967
Well, Amo, actually,
we're your supporters.

305
00:18:55,133 --> 00:18:56,867
- Thank you.
- Yes.

306
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,100
Ah, maybe we can solicit.

307
00:18:58,233 --> 00:19:00,067
Mister, you're so stubborn.

308
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,600
Well, tomorrow...

309
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:05,467
No problem with Amo. He'll just
rest for now. Tomorrow.

310
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,433
Amo. I'll take care of it.

311
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:10,833
And what time is it anyway?

312
00:19:10,967 --> 00:19:12,400
You know, come back tomorrow.

313
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:14,067
Okay, I'll take care of that.

314
00:19:15,033 --> 00:19:16,100
Okay, Idol.

315
00:19:16,233 --> 00:19:19,233
- Yes, okay, we'll come back.
- Thank you very much.

316
00:19:19,367 --> 00:19:20,900
But we're your fans.

317
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:23,533
- Thank you. I'm sorry.
- Thank you.

318
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:27,433
Why did you send them away?

319
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:28,767
Think about the votes
that will be wasted.

320
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:32,667
Well, yes, Amo, but I saw
the guy they were with earlier.

321
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,467
He's a policeman.

322
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:37,400
Well, I thought maybe those guys
had some other agenda with you,

323
00:19:37,533 --> 00:19:38,367
so never mind.

324
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,267
You take care of it.

325
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,200
They're annoying.

326
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,667
Bon!

327
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:50,400
Bon!

328
00:19:51,867 --> 00:19:52,433
Bon!

329
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:55,767
Amo is looking for us.

330
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:56,633
Where is he?

331
00:19:56,767 --> 00:19:57,833
He's in the office upstairs.

332
00:19:57,967 --> 00:19:59,067
- Let's go, let's go.
- Let's go.

333
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:08,800
Amo's office is upstairs.

334
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,467
You said Amo was upstairs.
He's not there.

335
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,133
I know he was there earlier.

336
00:20:48,267 --> 00:20:49,133
Come on, let's go find him.

337
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:49,767
Let's go.

338
00:21:15,967 --> 00:21:17,800
Good evening, Ma'am, Sir.

339
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:20,700
Reservation for Sergeant Garcia.

340
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:22,133
This way, Sir.

341
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,400
Thank you.

342
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:37,167
So, do you like the place?

343
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:38,233
Cause I like it.

344
00:21:39,467 --> 00:21:42,900
I like it,
but it's a bit too much.

345
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:45,067
I wish we could just have
coffee.

346
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:48,633
I thought about that too,

347
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:52,433
but you're better suited
for places like this.

348
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:54,567
Just like me,
I think I'm suited for you.

349
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,133
Thank you.

350
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:08,133
Do you want...

351
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:11,267
beef, astro...

352
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,433
astronaut?

353
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:13,500
Do you want fries?

354
00:22:13,633 --> 00:22:15,233
They have delicious fries here.

355
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,067
- Fries, we can have fries.
- Yeah.

356
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:19,633
You can choose whatever you
like.

357
00:23:20,267 --> 00:23:21,133
Enriquez?

358
00:23:23,300 --> 00:23:23,833
Roman!

359
00:23:27,267 --> 00:23:27,967
Roman!

360
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:32,667
Roman, come on.

361
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,700
Hey, Amo.

362
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:37,600
Let's drink.

363
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:39,767
Let's drink.

364
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,967
Where's Tonyo?
Didn't you drink him earlier?

365
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,533
He's already wasted.

366
00:23:47,667 --> 00:23:48,133
Maybe...

367
00:23:48,267 --> 00:23:49,233
Maybe he just peed.

368
00:23:50,833 --> 00:23:52,633
Get me some cash
from the cabinet.

369
00:23:52,767 --> 00:23:55,333
P200,000 and bring it to me.

370
00:23:57,133 --> 00:23:58,633
Yes, Amo.

371
00:23:58,767 --> 00:23:59,567
Got it.

372
00:24:10,233 --> 00:24:11,033
Enriquez?

373
00:24:11,167 --> 00:24:11,667
Sir?

374
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:16,367
Enriquez, what are you doing
here?

375
00:24:24,133 --> 00:24:26,467
Sir, here.

376
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,167
Enriquez, wait a minute.

377
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,033
Don't go there.

378
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,200
They're going up there.

379
00:24:31,067 --> 00:24:32,267
Here, here, here.

380
00:24:50,667 --> 00:24:52,167
Oh, the key...

381
00:26:13,867 --> 00:26:16,233
Boss, is there a problem?

382
00:26:16,367 --> 00:26:17,800
Our friend is inside.
Ouch!

383
00:26:17,933 --> 00:26:18,867
Your friend?

384
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,167
It's Tonyo, Boss.

385
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:21,500
I thought you could do it?

386
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:22,633
That was earlier, going down.

387
00:26:22,767 --> 00:26:23,600
Now I have to climb up.

388
00:26:23,733 --> 00:26:25,233
How am I going to get up there?
It's high.

389
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:25,900
Tonyo?

390
00:26:26,033 --> 00:26:27,033
What are you doing there?

391
00:26:27,167 --> 00:26:28,400
Why would you do that?

392
00:26:28,533 --> 00:26:31,000
I just asked my men
to follow you around.

393
00:26:31,133 --> 00:26:32,800
Who knows if that idiot cop,

394
00:26:32,933 --> 00:26:33,967
you're dating takes you
to a motel?

395
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:35,000
Why?

396
00:26:35,133 --> 00:26:37,200
I can't go on a date without you
following me?

397
00:26:37,333 --> 00:26:38,400
You know what to do.

398
00:26:38,533 --> 00:26:39,300
I'll take care of it.

399
00:26:39,433 --> 00:26:40,867
I'll plant tomorrow too.

400
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:42,200
I have an IED supplier.

401
00:26:42,367 --> 00:26:43,733
Go home!

402
00:26:43,867 --> 00:26:45,233
Get out!
